data.description: All the advantages of country living, near shopping & an incredibly enjoyable commute to Metro Denver as you pass by the horse farms & occasional wildlife & a view of the mountains & Pikes Peak that is breathtaking. The two-acre lot includes a large fenced pasture with water & the neighborhood offers great riding trails. You enter the home from a large open yard with a long porch across the front of the home. To the left of the front door is the large formal dining room. The spacious eat-in kitchen has been recently updated & includes a pantry. The laundry room is adjacent to the kitchen on the main floor & has additional pantry space. The large living room has a vaulted ceiling & includes a wood fireplace & looks out the upgraded French doors into the back yard. The master bedroom at the end of the hall has two closets, one of which is a large walk-in closet. The in suite bathroom has been recently renovated. It has a double vanity, a large, walk-in shower, & a soaking tub. A second set of recently upgraded French doors take you out onto the large deck, great for entertaining & BBQs. Two additional bedrooms & a full guest bathroom complete the main floor of the home.  The basement includes a large bedroom, a full bathroom & a small work-out room or den adjacent to the huge family room. It also has a kitchenette which has a sink & second refrigerator &, with some additional plug-in appliances, has served as a complete kitchen. This could make a great mother-in-law or guest house set up for family or friends. Storage space abounds & shelving is included. Vegetable garden, storage shed, lawn tractor with cart & a snow blower are all included. Here are the upgrades & additions recently completed: New Furnace & A/C(2021); New septic tank(Sep 2023); New well pressure tank & Whole house water filter(Nov 2023); Newer kitchen microwave; Two sets of French doors(2019); Impact resistant roof(2016); Water heater(2016); Exterior & most of the interior painted(2023)
